===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*d-puːk||belly; vitals; hollow object; cave}}; cognate with {{och-l|𥨍|cave}}, {{cog|bo|ཕུགས||innermost parts}}, {{cog|my|ဗိုက်||belly; pregnancy}}, {{m|my|အပေါက်|t=hole}}, {{cog|cdm|तुक्‌||t=belly; stomach}}, {{cog|tbq-bdg-pro|*bi(ʔ)-buk|*bi(ʔ)-'''buk'''|guts}}, Cogtse {{cog|sit-sit|tr=tə-pōk|t=belly}}, Brag-bar {{cog|sit-sit|tr=tə-vōk|t=belly}}, {{cog|sit-tan-pro|*puk||heart}} (STEDT; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}; {{zh-ref|Zhang, Jacques, and Lai, 2019}}).

Also compare {{cog|aav|-}} words: {{cog|mkh-pro|*bo()k||belly}}, {{cog|km|ពោះ||belly}}, {{cog|vi|bụng||belly}}({{zh-ref|Shorto, 2006}}; {{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

